Preheat your oven to 200°C. Halve the @salad potatoes{350%g} widthways. Put the potatoes onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer, cut-side down. When the oven is hot, roast the potatoes on the top shelf, ~{20%minutes}.

Wrap each @chicken breasts{2%British} with 2 rashers of @streaky bacon{6%British}. Trim the @carrot{2} then halve lengthways (no need to peel). Chop into roughly 1cm wide, 5cm long batons.

Lay the chicken and carrots onto another large baking tray. Drizzle the carrots with oil, season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat. Roast on the middle shelf until cooked through, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn the carrots halfway through.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, chop the remaining bacon into 1cm wide strips.

While everything cooks, pour the @water{150%ml} into a #saucepan{}. Bring to the boil, then stir in the @red wine jus paste{22%g}. Reduce the heat slightly, then bubble away until the sauce has reduced by half, ~{5-6%minutes}. Once glossy and thickened, remove from the heat. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed. Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a garlic press).

When the potatoes have cooked for 20 mins, remove them from the oven. Use the bottom of a #bowl{} or pan to lightly crush each potato half. Drizzle with more oil and return to the top shelf until crispy and golden, ~{10-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Add the chopped bacon to the pan and fry until browned, ~{3-4%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat. Cook bacon thoroughly.

Turn the heat down to medium, then stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute}. Add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry until piping hot, ~{2-3%minutes}. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then set aside.

When everything is ready, drizzle the @honey{15%g} over the carrots and toss to coat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop it in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

Serve up your ultimate bacon wrapped roast chicken breast with the smashed potatoes, honeyed carrots and peas alongside. Reheat the red wine jus if needed, then spoon over the chicken to serve. Enjoy!